Egyptian Stocks: Amer Group and Ezz Steel Are Active

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-19T12:09:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/egyptian-stocks-amer-group-and-ezz-steel-are-active.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
declined for a second day, retreating 0.8 percent to 5,135.99 at
:42 p.m. in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Amer Group (AMER EY), an Egyptian developer and operator of
resorts and restaurants, dropped 2.1 percent to 1.39 Egyptian
pounds, heading for the lowest close in almost a week. Egypt
received 42 percent less tourists from the  Persian Gulf  in June
compared with a year-earlier, Ahram Online reported, citing Sami
Mahmoud, head of the international department at the Tourism
Development Authority.  Ezz Steel (ESRS EY) lost 2.1 percent to 9.76 pounds, poised
for the lowest close in two months. Egypt’s biggest publicly
traded steel producer said its annual 2010 standalone profit
fell 53 percent to 116.1 million pounds ($19 million). Egypt’s
bourse said July 6 it gave the Cairo-based company 15 days to
report 2010 and first-quarter results, or face a trading
suspension.  Ezz Steel (ESRS)  hasn’t released 2010 consolidated results
or first-quarter figures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Dubai at 
